obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (96115)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_0_000010_202517_1746601226831&sectionId=96115&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_0_000010_202517_1746601226831
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Protection of Interests in`
  line `Aircraft Objects Act, 2025.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 1st day of May, 2025, vide notification No. S.O. 1937 (E), dated 30th day of April, 2025, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary,`
  line `Part II, sec. 3 (ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (96116)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_0_000010_202517_1746601226831&sectionId=96116&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_0_000010_202517_1746601226831
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `(1) In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,---`
  line
  line `(a) "agreement" shall have the meaning assigned to it in Article 1(a) of the Convention;`
  line
  line `(b) "aircraft" shall have the meaning assigned to it in Article I (2)(a) of the Protocol;`
  line
  line `(c) "aircraft objects" shall have the meaning assigned to it in Article I (2)(c) of the Protocol;`
  line
  line `(d) "Article" means an Article of the Convention or the Protocol;`
  line
  line `(e) "Convention" means the Convention on International Interests in Mobile Equipment`
  line `signed at Cape Town on 16th November, 2001, as set out in the First Schedule to this Act;`
  line
  line `(f) "creditor" shall have the meaning assigned to it in Article 1(i) of the Convention;`
  line
  line `(g) "debtor" shall have the meaning assigned to it in Article 1(j) of the Convention;`
  line
  line `(h) "declaration" means a declaration made by India under the Convention or the Protocol, as`
  line `set out in the Second Schedule to this Act;`
  line
  line `(i) "declared default" means the date on which the registry authority is notified by the creditor`
  line `of the occurrence of default;`
  line
  line `(j) "international interest" shall have the meaning assigned to it in Article 1(o) of the`
  line Convention;
  line
  line `(k) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(l) "Protocol" means the Protocol to the Convention on International Interests in Mobile`
  line `Equipment on Matters specific to Aircraft Equipment signed at Cape Town on 16th November,`
  line `2001, as set out in the Third Schedule to this Act;`
  line
  line `(m) "registry authority" means the Directorate General of Civil Aviation constituted under`
  line `section 3 of the Bharatiya Vayuyan Adhiniyam, 2024 (16 of 2024).`
  line
  line `(2) The words and expressions used and not defined in this Act, but defined in the Convention or`
  line `the Protocol or the regulations made thereunder, shall have the meanings respectively assigned to them`
  line `in the Convention, Protocol or regulations made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (96117)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Application of Convention and Protocol in India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_0_000010_202517_1746601226831&sectionId=96117&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_0_000010_202517_1746601226831
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this Act, the`
  line `Convention and Protocol shall have the force of law in India, in respect of the aircraft objects and in`
  line `accordance with the declarations deposited by India.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (96118)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Power of registry authority to issue directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_0_000010_202517_1746601226831&sectionId=96118&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_0_000010_202517_1746601226831
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `The registry authority may issue necessary`
  line `directions, for implementation of the provisions of the Convention and Protocol, including the`
  line `provisions given force of law under section 3, in such manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (96119)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Obligation of debtor and creditor to an agreement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_0_000010_202517_1746601226831&sectionId=96119&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_0_000010_202517_1746601226831
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) A debtor shall maintain and submit`
  line `to the registry authority, records of dues arising from, related to or owed in regard to the ownership or`
  line `use by the owner or operator of the aircraft object, in such form and manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) A creditor shall not be entitled to exercise any remedy under the Convention or Protocol unless`
  line `such creditor declares the occurrence of default by notifying the registry authority, in such form and`
  line `manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (96120)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Remedies on insolvency.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_0_000010_202517_1746601226831&sectionId=96120&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_0_000010_202517_1746601226831
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of Article XI of the Protocol, subject to the`
  line `declaration deposited by India, shall apply, mutatis mutandis, for remedies on insolvency under any law`
  line `for the time being in force:`
  line
  line `Provided that---`
  line
  line `(a) the debtor of the agreement is a---`
  line
  line `(i) body corporate or firm, incorporated or registered in India; or`
  line
  line `(ii) person, domiciled in or has his principal place of business in India;`
  line
  line `(b) the international interest of the agreement has been registered in accordance with the`
  line `Convention and Protocol; and`
  line
  line `(c) the debtor and creditor have not by written agreement excluded the application of this`
  line section.
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (96121)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `De-registration and export request authorisation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_0_000010_202517_1746601226831&sectionId=96121&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_0_000010_202517_1746601226831
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of the Bharatiya`
  line `Vayuyan Adhiniyam, 2024 (16 of 2024), or any rules made thereunder, the provisions of Article XIII`
  line `of the Protocol shall apply to the de-registration and export request.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (96122)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title Jurisdiction.
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_0_000010_202517_1746601226831&sectionId=96122&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_0_000010_202517_1746601226831
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything in any other law for the time being in force, the High`
  line `Court having territorial jurisdiction shall be the relevant court for the purposes of Article 53 of the`
  line Convention.
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (96123)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Provisions of Act to have overriding effect.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_0_000010_202517_1746601226831&sectionId=96123&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_0_000010_202517_1746601226831
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) In the case of any inconsistency between a`
  line `provision of this Act and any other law for the time being in force, the provisions of this Act shall`
  line `prevail to the extent of such inconsistency.`
  line
  line `(2) Save as otherwise provided in this Act, the provisions of this Act shall be in addition to, and`
  line `not in derogation of any other law for the time being in force.`
  line
  line `(3) The provisions of this Act or the Convention or the Protocol shall not affect the rights of the`
  line `Central Government or any entity thereof, or other provider of public services in India, or any`
  line `intergovernmental organisation in which India is a member, to arrest or detain an aircraft object under`
  line `any law for the time being in force, for payment of any amount due to the Government of India or any`
  line `such entity or provider of public services or organisation, directly relating to the service or services`
  line `provided by it in respect of that aircraft objects.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (96124)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Power of Central Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_0_000010_202517_1746601226831&sectionId=96124&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_0_000010_202517_1746601226831
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, make rules, as may be considered necessary and expedient, for`
  line `carrying out the provisions of this Act or implementation of the provisions of the Convention or`
  line Protocol.
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) manner to issue directions under section 4;`
  line
  line `(b) form and manner under sub-sections (1) and (2) of section 5.`
  line
  line `(3) The power to make rules under this section is subject to the condition of the rules being made`
  line `after previous publication:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may, in the public interest, by order in writing, dispense`
  line `with the condition of previous publication in any case.`
  line
  line `(4) Every rule made under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be, after it is made before each`
  line `House of Parliament while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in`
  line `one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any`
  line `modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter`
  line `have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any`
  line `such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (96125)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Power of Central Government in respect of declarations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_0_000010_202517_1746601226831&sectionId=96125&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_0_000010_202517_1746601226831
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government`
  line `may make, amend or withdraw any declaration, or any subsequent declaration in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of the Convention or Protocol.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government, to give effect to any declaration or subsequent declaration made,`
  line `amended or withdrawn under the Convention or the Protocol, may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, amend the Second Schedule to this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
